    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2006 Lancer Evolution IX MR is a superlative example of the CT9A chassis, preserved in its factory-original configuration. The legendary 4G63 power plant features MIVEC variable valve timing and a twin-scroll TD05HR turbocharger, providing immediate spool and a broad power band. Power is delivered through the MR-specific close-ratio six-speed manual gearbox and a sophisticated drivetrain utilizing an Active Center Differential (ACD) with three selectable modes for optimal torque distribution. The suspension geometry remains true to stock specifications, featuring factory-tuned Bilstein monotube dampers and forged BBS lightweight alloys. The braking system, headlined by four-piston Brembo calipers and ventilated rotors, remains in pristine condition with no signs of glazing or thermal cycling. This is a collector-grade unit with zero modifications, offering the precise mechanical feedback and rally-derived dynamics that defined an era of performance engineering.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 34
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Garage kept. Full service records. No accidents.",
      "price": 44000.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
